Group: FedNow Service
Collection: FedNow Service Release 1
Usage Guideline: AccountDebitCreditNotification_camt.054.001.08
Base Message: camt.054.001.08
Date of publication: 01 June 2023
URL: https://www2.swift.com/mystandards/#/mp/mx/_kijaUKEYEeuB-v2uhrZqSw/_qR07TZ5FEeyNX8SYmSuaLA
Description: FedNow Service Scope

An account debit credit notification is the message the FedNow Service uses to provide a FedNow correspondent with real-time notice of a value message that was processed and settled by the FedNow Service for a FedNow participant that is a respondent of the correspondent (or in rarer cases a respondent of the correspondent bank’s respondent).

FedNow Service Usage

The account debit credit notification may be used by FedNow correspondents for reconciliation purposes.

The FedNow Service will send account debit credit notifications on an opt-in basis, i.e., financial institutions providing correspondent services will need to sign up to receive this notice of their respondent(s)’s payments.
